data.description: This historic home, built in 1900, is waiting for you to make it your own. As you step on thecovered front stoop and enter the front door, you will fall in love with the beadboardceiling in the hallway. The generous living room is just to your right. Original flooring, naturallighting, and a fireplace round out this room. This home also boasts a dining room with built-in cabinetry to display your family heirlooms. The kitchen has granite countertops and lighting to make for easy meal prep and cooking. Eat evening meals at the kitchen bar or entertain family and friends. You will love the exposed brick next to the coffee bar area. Just off the kitchen is another area that could be used for storage, entertaining, or use your imagination! The laundry room, just to the left, has plenty of space for a washer and dryer as well as storage of cleaning items. At the back of the entry hallway is a half bath for guests. Upstairs are three nice-sized bedrooms with plenty of windows to allow for natural light to shine through. Pine flooring and molding, along with the original banister, give this home lots of character. The tiled bath has a tub with two vanities and a rain shower head. The backyard can be an oasis for evening drinks or a morning cup of coffee. Enjoy everything downtown New Bern has to offer, as this home is just a short walk to Tryon Palace, the NC History Museum, and other points of interest. Come make this home your own. Call for your private showing today.
